      • getJavaCollection

        public JavaCollectionOfMany<T> getJavaCollection()
        Returns the Java collection in which this builder collected the desired objects. When this method is called, this builder is used up, so its Java collection is set to null. This way, it is ensured that the created Java collection is no more appended, which makes it possible for Collection implementations to use it directly instead of copying it (for optimization).
        Returns:
        the Java collection in which this builder collected the desired objects
